         <head>
            <ce:title>On the calculation of single ionic activity coefficients by Kirkwood—Buff theory: comments</ce:title>
            <ce:author-group>
               <ce:author>
                  <ce:given-name>Denver G.</ce:given-name>
                  <ce:surname>Hall</ce:surname>
               </ce:author>
               <ce:affiliation>
                  <ce:textfn>Unilever Research Port Sunlight Laboratory, Quarry Road East, Bebington, Wirral, Merseyside L63 3JW, UK</ce:textfn>
               </ce:affiliation>
            </ce:author-group>
            <ce:date-received day="11" month="9" year="1990"/>
            <ce:date-revised day="5" month="11" year="1990"/>
            <ce:abstract class="author">
               <ce:section-title>Abstract</ce:section-title>
               <ce:abstract-sec>
                  <ce:simple-para view="all" id="simple-para.0010">An expression derived recently describing the dependence of single ionic activity coefficients on solution composition is compared with earlier work. The condition that must be met for the two approaches to be compatible is derived and shown to apply to a solution in which the ions associate to form a series of charged complex species whose distribution functions conform to Debye—Hückel theory.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:abstract-sec>
            </ce:abstract>
